Package bankteller.demo1

Class BankTellerController

java.lang.Object
bankteller.demo1.BankTellerController
public class BankTellerController extends Object
This class controls the actions on bank accounts in the Bank Teller. Account holders can open, close, deposit to, and withdraw from their account, as well as view a list of all current accounts in the database and update balances based on fees.
Author:
Afsana Rahman, Mini Sinha

    • validBirthday

      private boolean validBirthday(String birthday)
      Checks if account holder has a valid birthday for opening a bank account. Valid birthdays for opening an account must be a valid past date.
      Parameters:
      birthday - String form of birthday
      Returns:
      true if the birthday is a possible birthday, false otherwise

    • findAccount

      private int findAccount(Account account)
      Method that finds a given account in the current AccountDatabase. An account is considered "found" if there exists an account of the same type (Checking, College Checking, Savings, Money Market) with the same holder. An account holder can only have one Checking OR College Checking account in the database, closed or not.
      Parameters:
      account - account to search for
      Returns:
      index where account is located in the AccountDatabase -- returns NOT_FOUND if it does not exist

    • open

      private void open(Account account)
      This method re/opens an account for a given account holder. An account is not valid for opening if the holder already has an open account of the same type in the database.
      Parameters:
      account - account to be opened

    • transaction

      void transaction()
      This method processes valid deposits and withdrawals into accounts in the account database.

    • validTransaction

      private boolean validTransaction()
      This method checks if user-inputted information is valid for a deposit or withdrawal.
      Returns:
      true if the transaction is possible, false otherwise

    • withdrawal

      private void withdrawal(Account account)
      This method processes a valid withdrawal from an existing account in the database. Withdrawals are only valid if the account holder has enough money to withdraw the given amount.
      Parameters:
      account - account being checked for possible withdrawal
